==English and Irish==

===Etymology===
The name ''Cú Roí'' probably means "hound of the battlefield."

===Proper Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''Cú Roí (mac Dáire)'''

#''Irish mythology.'' A king of [[Munster]] and a [[sorceror]] who can [[transform]] at will. He was killed by [[Cúchulainn]], but his death was avenged by his son [[Lugaid mac Con Roí]], who was subsequently killed by [[Conall the Victorious]].

